    "story":  [
                  "At the very summit, \u003cb\u003eQuince\u003c/b\u003e bagged the pasting of the tournament so far, Sweden (tall, blond and flat-pack efficient) romping home 5-1. Borderline rude. Hot on their heels, \u003cb\u003eBig Pewerk\u003c/b\u003e is hauling Iraq (all passion, light on polish) around like a dead fridge up a fire escape \u0026mdash; it\u0027s played, and contributed the square root of sod all. Rounding out the smug end of the table, \u003cb\u003eEllie\u003c/b\u003e is the undisputed sultan of the stalemate: 5 draws and counting. Edge-of-the-seat stuff it is not.",
                  "Wading into the midtable swamp, \u003cb\u003eSid\u003c/b\u003e is grinding out 3 clean sheets like a man morally opposed to fun \u0026mdash; ugly, effective, and a touch boring. Keeping them grim company, \u003cb\u003eEtan\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s lot have collectively decided defending is for cowards \u0026mdash; 11 goals banged in (GD -2), spearheaded by England (bravely marching toward an inevitable penalty heartbreak). And clinging on by their fingernails, \u003cb\u003eElsa\u003c/b\u003e is running a full-blown one-nation hostage situation \u0026mdash; USA (calling it soccer with their whole chest) alone props up 55% of their points, and if that lot trip over their laces the whole house of cards flutters off into the sea.",
                  "Down in the cheap seats, \u003cb\u003eMurray\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s backline has the structural integrity of a wet paper bag \u0026mdash; 13 shipped already, with Croatia (old, wily, and will run you into the turf) alone waving in 4. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, \u003cb\u003eIke\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s pride and joy is a tidy 3-1 spanking from France (world-beaters one dressing-room row from civil war) \u0026mdash; ruthless, efficient, faintly smug."
              ],
